[2] Neck blast - USA: Arkansas
Date: Tue 27 Aug 2013
Source: ArkansasMatters [edited]
http://www.arkansasmatters.com/story/farmers-battling-neck-blast-in-greene-co-rice-field/d/story/VOGRQn7Z4EitSgJnaK5uwA


Some Northeast Arkansas rice farmers are battling a plant disease in their fields known as neck blast.

The disease that can prevent rice grains from filling out has been confirmed in a field in western Greene County, prompting a warning to scout late rice fields.

The warning is for "late-planted fields with blast-susceptible varieties in blast-prone areas," says Yeshi Wamishe, extension plant pathologist.

"If you have rice fields at booting to early heading, the crop could still benefit from a fungicide application," she says. "Timing is important -- once the head is completely out of the boot, a fungicide application has no benefit for prevention of neck or panicle blast."

[More information via http://www.arkansas-crops.com/2013/08/25/blast-alert-in-ne-arkansas/]

