[3] Brown spot - India: Jammu and Kashmir
Date: Thu 29 Aug 2013
Source: Greater Kashmir [edited]
http://www.greaterkashmir.com/news/2013/Aug/30/measures-afoot-to-curb-disease-of-paddy-crop-3.asp


In view of reports of blast and brown spot disease that has attacked paddy crop in certain areas of Baramulla, Kupwara, Budgam and Anantnag [districts], the Agriculture Department has initiated measures to curb the diseases.

Farmers are provided fungicides free of cost to control the diseases. Sprays of fungicides have been carried out by the department in the affected areas. The Director of Agriculture Kashmir has advised farmers to contact the Extension Officers of their respective areas in case they find any symptoms on the paddy crop.

